06/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministries of Bulgaria and Macedonia have decided to establish a hotline aimed at boosting collaboration. An agreement to that effect was signed Tuesday (5 October), during Macedonian Interior Minister Siljan Avramovski's visit to Sofia. The countries also agreed to boost efforts in the fight against organised crime and global terrorism. (Dnevnik - 06/10/04; Makfax - 05/10/04)
